fields.title: The Mushroom Hunter's Tarot
fields.details: The Mushroom Hunters Tarot is a 78-card mushroom-themed tarot deck, each card represented by its own unique mushroom. Ever since moving up to the Pacific Northwest several years ago, Ive become fascinated by the world of mushrooms. Theyre full of such magic and wonder and the more I learn about them the more I realize that each mushroom has its own story to tell, its own purpose in our world. And what better way to tell their stories than through the art of tarot?

fields.title: Move Reclining Liberty to Jersey City!
fields.details: You might have seen Reclining Liberty in Morningside Park this past yearor in the New York Times, Gothamist, Time Out New York; American, Russian, and Japanese television; and in your social media feed with your friends dogs (or cats). This popular sculpture by Zaq Landsberg, a 25-foot-long mashup of the Statue of Liberty and reclining Buddha statues of Asia, has completed its stay in Harlem and now has the chance to be installed at Liberty State Park in Jersey City, NJ for one year.

fields.title: Kirby Hard Enamel Pins & Stationary
fields.details: This is my first Kickstarter project! And I'm very excited and nervous at how this campaign will do, but I have taken a lot of time to design the pins and other rewards/items that are available! I absolutely love Kirby so, I thought it was only fitting that my first campaign be Kirby themed! I hope you like not only the pin designs but the other items offered as well! I have wanted to create/offer pins since opening my Etsy shop but I have been held back by the cost of production (pin production is not cheap!). Hence why I am here!

fields.title: Robert Weiss: In Preparation for the Museum
fields.details: My name is Robert Weiss. I am a teacher, filmmaker, and painter living in Dallas, Texas. I have painted since I was a student at Booker T. Washington High School for the Performing and Visual Arts, with further studies at the Maryland Institute College of Art and Syracuse University, where I received my Masters in Painting. I currently teach film and painting at the Episcopal School of Dallas, and spend evenings and weekends painting in my studio. Lately, I have been working overtime in the studio to prepare for an exciting opportunity.

fields.title: King of the Kongo (1929): Restored Complete 35mm Serial
fields.details: The King of the Kongo is a 1929 cliffhanger serial, designed to be seen in a theater-- one episode every week. This was the very first sound serial. In those days, the sound was not recorded on film in the way it would have been just a couple of years later. It was recorded on shellac discs and carefully shipped to theaters.
